History.Uddron's Cultists:
{{Quote
|Master Uddron has seen the future, Nerys. [[The Absolute]] will remake the world.
|Father Alby
}}
Prior to or during [[1492 DR]], Uddron Blass had infiltrated Baldur's Gate.{{Cite comic/Mindbreaker 1}} A fight broke out between the heroes and the cult members. Father [[Alby]], a former [[Kelemvorite]], attempted to convince [[Nerys]] that the master, Uddron, had foreseen future events, and wished to show her their abilities. The heroes, however, managed to escape.

History.Uddron Steps In:
{{Quote
|This pair has proven to be quite ''resourceful''. Now their skills shall serve the ''Absolute''... Prepare them for ''enlightenment''.
|Uddron to the downed heroes
}}
[[Shandie]], with [[Minsc]] (and [[Boo]]!) and Nerys in tow, approached a man known as [[Fetcher]] to acquire information about Master Uddron. He, however, did not know more than they did about the hidden master. At that point, Uddron's mindwitness appeared, along with a group of cultists, but they were slain after a battle. The other two heroes, [[Krydle]] and [[Delina]], were attacked by another group of cultists, but Uddron Blass stepped in and blasted them with great [[psionic]] energy.

History.Captured Heroes:
{{Quote
|Whatever ''defiant spirit'' you think you have will crumble in a few hours or a few days. The gestation time ''varies'', but the results are always the same. A pronounced sense of ''unity''. Let's find out...
|Master Uddron on a special sort of [[ceremorphosis]].
}}
Master Uddron successfully captured Krydle, Delina, and [[Coran]], and had them chained up underneath the [[High Hall]]. Uddron revealed that a [[Flaming Fist]] captain belonged to them. Here, Blass tapped into Krydle's mind, turning him against his father, and showing him visions of [[nautiloid]]s pouring out a void. In a burst of [[wild magic]] energy, Uddron and Delina disappeared from the room, leaving the two adventurers behind with the displacer beast. As the beast was taken down, Coran and Krydle escaped.{{Cite comic/Mindbreaker 4}}
